.TH start-cli-backup-policy-apply 1  "apply "
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-backup\-policy\-apply \- Apply an automatic backup retention policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli backup policy apply\fR [\fB\-\-keep\-tier\fR] [\fB\-\-latest\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-confirm\-removal\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fITARGET_ID\fR> <\fIPACKAGE_ID\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Apply an automatic backup retention policy
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-keep\-tier\fR \fI<INTERVAL:COVERAGE>\fR
Retention tier INTERVAL:COVERAGE; accepts s, m, h, d, or w and may repeat
.TP
\fB\-\-latest\-only\fR
Keep only the latest automatic checkpoint
.TP
\fB\-\-confirm\-removal\fR \fI<CHECKPOINT_ID>\fR
Checkpoint ID reported by preview\-change; repeat for every removal
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR

.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fITARGET_ID\fR>
Backup target identifier
.TP
<\fIPACKAGE_ID\fR>
Package identifier
